{
	"name": "Edict of the Oath",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/magic/fire/orb-fireball-puzzle.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>You seal oaths in fire. As part of casting this edict, two or more creatures must voluntarily agree to an oath or contract in your presence. When they do, the terms are written in your inner flame. You know whenever a creature breaks the Oath, and you can choose to inflict a punishment over them. If they break the oath, they are cursed and they start burning. When you choose to punish them, they take 1d8 fire damage at the start of each of their turn.</p><p>The Oath is totally broken after a creature takes more than your total level multiplied by 5 damage in this way. You can't use this edict while another oath is active. </p>",
